
                                            Raymond Dusabe was found dead in his Sea Point flat on Monday. 
                                         CAPE TOWN - A man will appear in the Cape Town magistrates court on Wednesday in connection with the murder of a Rwandan doctor.  Raymond Dusabe was found dead in his Sea Point flat on Monday.  Western Cape police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana says that a 29-year-old man has been arrested.  “A case of murder has been opened for investigation by Sea Point police. He faces a charge of murder.” Dusabe, who did his post graduate studies at Stellenbosch University, was Rwanda’s first-ever gynaecological oncologist. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)